[[File:Stephen lovely september 15.jpg|thumb]] '''Stephen Lovely''' (born 1966, [[Dallas, Texas]]) is an American [[novelist]] and [[educator]]. He attended [[Kenyon College]] and the [[Iowa Writers' Workshop]], where he studied with Deborah Eisenberg, Margot Livesey, Ethan Canin, and Frank Conroy.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://iowayoungwritersstudio.org/program/director/|website = Iowa Young Writers' Studio|access-date = 2016-01-26|title = bio from Iowa Young Writers' Studio}}</ref> His first novel, ''Irreplaceable'', was published by Hyperion/Voice in 2009 and translated into German, Dutch, and Chinese. ''Irreplaceable'' received the Dana Award for the Novel and a James Michener-Copernicus Society of America Award. Since 2005 Stephen has been the director of the [http://iowayoungwritersstudio.org/ Iowa Young Writers' Studio], a summer, residential creative writing program for high school students at [[University of Iowa|The University of Iowa]].
